00:41:46.202 --> 00:41:49.581
- Whoa! Whoa!
- <i>(Baby giggles)</i>

476
00:41:53.710 --> 00:41:55.545
- I got it now.
- <i>(Laughs)</i>

477
00:41:57.088 --> 00:41:58.715
So where'd you learn
to be a dancer?

478
00:41:59.925 --> 00:42:02.761
Well, this guy came into
this luncheonette one day,

479
00:42:02.844 --> 00:42:06.681
and we were all sitting around
doing nothing.

480
00:42:06.765 --> 00:42:10.727
And he said that Arthur Murray
was giving a test for instructors.

481
00:42:10.810 --> 00:42:13.104
So, if you passed...

482
00:42:16.942 --> 00:42:18.818
they teach you all these
different kinds of dances,

483
00:42:18.902 --> 00:42:21.571
show you how to break them down,
how to teach them, you know.

484
00:42:25.784 --> 00:42:27.118
What?

485
00:42:29.871 --> 00:42:31.039
No.

486
00:42:36.544 --> 00:42:38.046
Good.

487
00:42:38.129 --> 00:42:40.715
No, no, don't look down.
Right here.

488
00:42:41.883 --> 00:42:42.717
Good.

489
00:42:42.801 --> 00:42:43.802
And...

490
00:42:45.053 --> 00:42:47.430
Whoo... <i>(Laughs)</i>

491
00:42:47.514 --> 00:42:49.516
<i>♪ ("Hey Baby" by
Bruce Channel playing) ♪</i>

492
00:43:27.137 --> 00:43:31.141
Now, bend your knees
and go up. Go, go.

493
00:43:31.224 --> 00:43:32.434
Good try.

494
00:43:32.517 --> 00:43:35.311
Now, you'll hurt me if you
don't trust me, all right?

495
00:43:35.395 --> 00:43:37.355
Now, go, go. Go.

496
00:43:39.816 --> 00:43:42.027
Good. Now, I'm gonna
go up, all right?

497
00:43:45.822 --> 00:43:47.240
<i>(Baby screams, laughs)</i>

498
00:43:49.367 --> 00:43:53.079
<i>(Johnny)</i> You know, the best place
to practice lifts is in the water.

499
00:43:53.163 --> 00:43:56.082
Just bend your knees.
And... go.

500
00:43:56.166 --> 00:43:57.709
Good.

501
00:43:57.792 --> 00:43:59.377
Good. Good.

502
00:43:59.461 --> 00:44:01.546
Now hold the position. Hold it.

503
00:44:01.629 --> 00:44:03.423
Good. Don't break! Don't break!

504
00:44:03.506 --> 00:44:04.424
<i>(Baby screams)</i>

505
00:44:06.217 --> 00:44:08.219
<i>(Both laughing)</i>

506
00:44:16.352 --> 00:44:17.395
<i>(Softly)</i> Okay.

507
00:44:17.479 --> 00:44:20.648
- All right, let's do it again.
- Okay.

508
00:44:20.732 --> 00:44:26.029
- Okay. All right. One, two, three.
- Okay.

509
00:44:27.030 --> 00:44:28.364
Oh, sorry.

510
00:44:30.033 --> 00:44:32.327
- Good. Keep-- No, don't.
- <i>(Yelps)</i>

511
00:44:34.537 --> 00:44:37.040
<i>(Laughing)</i>

512
00:44:46.633 --> 00:44:48.176
It's not too bad.

513
00:44:52.222 --> 00:44:54.641
- One more time.
- Okay. Over my head. Go.

514
00:44:57.310 --> 00:44:59.270
I can't believe it's tonight.

515
00:44:59.354 --> 00:45:02.482
The Sheldrake's 20 minutes away.
We'll change in the car.

516
00:45:02.565 --> 00:45:05.068
<i>(Gasps)</i>

517
00:45:05.151 --> 00:45:06.528
Mrs. Schumacher!

518
00:45:06.611 --> 00:45:08.571
Hey, Mrs. Schumacher.
Hey, wait, we'll help you.

519
00:45:10.323 --> 00:45:13.034
<i>(Mrs. Schumacher)</i>
Such junk. Such junk.

520
00:45:13.118 --> 00:45:14.494
<i>(Laughs)</i>

521
00:45:14.577 --> 00:45:17.747
Benny Bernstein's Dancing School,
Avenue B.

522
00:45:17.831 --> 00:45:19.541
That's where I went.

523
00:45:19.624 --> 00:45:22.752
George Burns was a teacher.

524
00:45:22.836 --> 00:45:24.003
Oh...

525
00:45:24.087 --> 00:45:25.547
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

526
00:45:31.261 --> 00:45:33.680
So I'll just keep
my shoulders down, my head up,

527
00:45:33.763 --> 00:45:36.891
my frame locked, stay on my toes...

528
00:45:36.975 --> 00:45:38.977
What if I forget the steps?

529
00:45:39.060 --> 00:45:42.605
Pull up, watch your frame.
And remember, let him lead you.

530
00:45:42.689 --> 00:45:46.985
I'm afraid I'm gonna forget to spike,
get dizzy and fall on my face.

531
00:45:47.068 --> 00:45:51.990
No. Don't look at my feet,
keep my head up, my eyes open,

532
00:45:52.073 --> 00:45:56.035
tension in my arms,
my frame locked, seat pulled up...

533
00:45:56.119 --> 00:45:57.704
Thanks, Baby.

534
00:46:00.582 --> 00:46:03.793
Look, I just want you to know
that I don't sleep around...

535
00:46:03.877 --> 00:46:06.921
whatever Robbie might have told you.

536
00:46:07.005 --> 00:46:09.174
And I thought that he loved me.

537
00:46:10.675 --> 00:46:12.594
I thought it was something special.

538
00:46:14.095 --> 00:46:16.764
Anyway, I just wanted you
to know that.

539
00:46:21.352 --> 00:46:23.479
So, how does it look?

540
00:46:23.563 --> 00:46:24.731
<i>(Sad chuckle)</i>

541
00:46:25.982 --> 00:46:27.233
<i>(Giggling)</i>

542
00:46:31.029 --> 00:46:32.655
I'm scared.

543
00:46:35.074 --> 00:46:37.118
I'm so scared, Baby.

544
00:46:38.411 --> 00:46:39.871
Don't worry.

545
00:46:40.997 --> 00:46:44.292
You'll be fine. You'll be fine.

546
00:46:48.379 --> 00:46:50.173
<i>(Stan)</i> Bingo! Bingo! Bingo!

547
00:46:50.256 --> 00:46:54.010
That's right, it's Thursday night
at Kellerman's. That's bingo night.

548
00:46:54.093 --> 00:46:57.847
- Hey, how about a dance later?
- Could be. Who knows?

549
00:46:57.931 --> 00:46:59.933
Lisa, you just gotta
do something for me.

550
00:47:00.016 --> 00:47:01.726
I don't just gonna do anything.

551
00:47:01.809 --> 00:47:03.519
Just tell Mommy and Daddy
I have a terrible headache

552
00:47:03.603 --> 00:47:05.396
and I'm in bed and check
on me once, okay?

553
00:47:08.274 --> 00:47:09.859
Bye.

554
00:47:11.903 --> 00:47:14.447
<i>(Emcee)</i> The Sheldrake Hotel
is proud to present

555
00:47:14.530 --> 00:47:16.366
Johnny Castle and partner

556
00:47:16.449 --> 00:47:18.618
in "Mambo Magic."

557
00:47:18.701 --> 00:47:21.955
<i>♪ ("De todo un poco" begins) ♪</i>

558
00:47:22.038 --> 00:47:23.581
Relax.

559
00:47:56.197 --> 00:47:57.907
Cross-body lead.

560
00:48:28.021 --> 00:48:29.272
Wrong way!

561
00:48:38.323 --> 00:48:40.116
Over here.

562
00:48:47.540 --> 00:48:49.334
Ready for the lift?

563
00:48:52.503 --> 00:48:53.379
Come on.

564
00:48:59.969 --> 00:49:01.554
Keep going. Keep going.

565
00:49:09.937 --> 00:49:11.439
<i>(Applause)</i>

566
00:49:22.116 --> 00:49:24.118
<i>(Applause continues)</i>

567
00:49:45.098 --> 00:49:46.974
<i>(DJ on radio)</i>
<i>...because wherever you are now,</i>

568
00:49:47.058 --> 00:49:49.394
<i>I want you to IBook at the sky.
Look at those stars.</i>

569
00:49:49.477 --> 00:49:52.397
<i>What a show.
Here are The Drifters.</i>

570
00:49:53.523 --> 00:49:55.441
You did good.
You worked hard.

571
00:49:55.525 --> 00:49:57.735
I saw that old couple from Kellerman's
and I thought that was it.

572
00:49:57.819 --> 00:49:59.904
Oh! Me too. Me too.

573
00:50:01.823 --> 00:50:04.534
You know, but by the second turn
you really had it.

574
00:50:04.617 --> 00:50:08.371
- But I didn't do the lift.
- You did real good.

575
00:50:09.789 --> 00:50:12.792
<i>♪ ("Some Kind of Wonderful"
by The Drifters playing) ♪</i>

576
00:50:21.008 --> 00:50:22.301
<i>(Groans)</i>

577
00:50:42.405 --> 00:50:42.447
<i>(Crickets chirping)</i>

578
00:51:04.510 --> 00:51:05.887
<i>(Whistles)</i>

579
00:51:10.266 --> 00:51:11.350
Thanks.

580
00:51:15.146 --> 00:51:16.689
Johnny!

581
00:51:16.772 --> 00:51:18.941
Come on. It's Penny.

582
00:51:21.527 --> 00:51:23.988
- She wouldn't go until you got back.
- You didn't call an ambulance?

583
00:51:24.071 --> 00:51:26.657
She said the hospital would call
the police. She made me promise.

584
00:51:26.741 --> 00:51:30.077
- <i>(Whimpering)</i>
- He didn't use no ether, nothing.

585
00:51:30.161 --> 00:51:31.996
I thought you said
he was a real M.D.?

586
00:51:32.079 --> 00:51:34.290
The guy had a dirty knife
and a folding table.

587
00:51:35.458 --> 00:51:37.043
I could hear her screaming
in the hallway.

588
00:51:37.126 --> 00:51:40.713
And I swear to God, Johnny,
I tried to get in. I tried!

589
00:51:40.796 --> 00:51:43.799
- <i>(Shuddering)</i>
- It's all right.

590
00:51:43.883 --> 00:51:45.593
Johnny's here.

591
00:51:58.564 --> 00:52:00.983
What? What is it, Baby?

592
00:52:02.443 --> 00:52:04.195
- Is it Lisa?
- No.

593
00:52:20.169 --> 00:52:23.631
Excuse me. Excuse me!
Everybody clear out, please.

594
00:52:24.715 --> 00:52:25.716
- <i>(Groaning)</i>
- Okay.

595
00:52:28.344 --> 00:52:29.929
<i>(Shuddering, sobbing)</i>

596
00:52:32.014 --> 00:52:33.599
Oh... <i>(Sobs)</i>

597
00:52:33.683 --> 00:52:37.520
Yes, I know that hurts.
We're gonna take care of that.

598
00:52:39.730 --> 00:52:40.856
<i>(Sighs)</i>

599
00:52:40.940 --> 00:52:44.235
- Who's responsible for this girl?
- I am.

600
00:52:44.318 --> 00:52:46.862
Please, is she--

601
00:52:53.786 --> 00:52:55.788
<i>(Crickets chirping)</i>

602
00:53:04.380 --> 00:53:06.465
Doc, thanks a lot.

603
00:53:06.549 --> 00:53:09.302
Dr. Houseman, I don't know
how to thank you, to tell you, to--

604
00:53:20.104 --> 00:53:21.439
Was that what my money paid for?

605
00:53:21.522 --> 00:53:23.316
Daddy, I'm sorry.
I never meant to lie.

606
00:53:23.399 --> 00:53:26.861
You're not the person I thought you were,
Baby. I'm not sure who you are.

607
00:53:26.944 --> 00:53:29.322
But I don't want you to have anything
to do with those people again.

608
00:53:29.405 --> 00:53:30.406
- Can I just explain--
- Nothing!

609
00:53:30.489 --> 00:53:33.451
You're to have nothing to do
with any of them ever again!

610
00:53:33.534 --> 00:53:37.538
I won't tell your mother about this.
Right now I'm going to bed.

611
00:53:37.622 --> 00:53:40.291
And take that stuff off your face
before your mother sees you!

612
00:53:43.669 --> 00:53:45.129
<i>(Owl hooting)</i>

613
00:53:45.212 --> 00:53:47.381
<i>(Marge)</i> Is everything
all right, Jake?

614
00:53:47.465 --> 00:53:49.800
It's all right, Marge.
Go back to sleep.

615
00:53:55.723 --> 00:53:59.268
<i>♪ ("These Arms of Mine"
by Otis Redding playing) ♪</i>

616
00:53:59.352 --> 00:54:00.895
<i>(Knock on door)</i>

617
00:54:11.238 --> 00:54:12.239
Can I come in?

618
00:54:24.877 --> 00:54:28.714
I got a-- I guess it's not a great room.
You probably got a great room.

619
00:54:28.798 --> 00:54:31.175
No. It's a great room!

620
00:54:43.104 --> 00:54:44.271
No, leave it on.

621
00:54:47.274 --> 00:54:49.402
I'm sorry about the way
my father treated you.

622
00:54:50.611 --> 00:54:53.989
No. Your father was great.

623
00:54:54.073 --> 00:54:57.034
He was great.
The way he took care of Penny--

624
00:54:57.118 --> 00:54:59.161
Yes, but I mean the way
he was with you.

625
00:55:00.871 --> 00:55:03.082
It's really me it has to do with.

626
00:55:05.126 --> 00:55:08.379
Johnny, I came here because my father--

627
00:55:08.462 --> 00:55:10.798
No. The way he saved her--

628
00:55:10.881 --> 00:55:12.466
I mean, I could never do
anything like that.

629
00:55:12.550 --> 00:55:14.051
That was something.

630
00:55:14.135 --> 00:55:16.512
I mean, the reason people treat me
like I'm nothing is because I'm nothing.

631
00:55:16.595 --> 00:55:20.391
That's not true! You--
You're everything!

632
00:55:21.559 --> 00:55:25.062
You don't understand the way it is
for somebody like me.

633
00:55:25.146 --> 00:55:27.231
Last month I'm eating jujubes
to keep alive.

634
00:55:27.314 --> 00:55:30.109
This month, women are stuffing
diamonds in my pockets.

635
00:55:30.192 --> 00:55:33.028
I'm balancing on shit and as quick
as that I can be down there again.

636
00:55:33.112 --> 00:55:36.657
No, it's not the way it is!
It doesn't have to be that way!

637
00:55:39.118 --> 00:55:40.828
I've never known anybody like you.

638
00:55:40.911 --> 00:55:42.580
You look at the world and you think
you can make it better.

639
00:55:42.663 --> 00:55:44.874
Somebody's lost, you find them.
Somebody's bleeding--

640
00:55:44.957 --> 00:55:48.794
And I go get my daddy.
That's really brave, like you said.

641
00:55:48.878 --> 00:55:51.714
That took a lot of guts
to go to him!

642
00:55:51.797 --> 00:55:53.883
I mean...
You are not scared of anything.

643
00:55:53.966 --> 00:55:57.511
Me? I'm scared of everything!
I'm scared of what I saw.

644
00:55:57.595 --> 00:56:01.182
I'm scared of what I did,
of who I am.

645
00:56:01.265 --> 00:56:04.101
And most of all, I'm scared
of walking out of this room

646
00:56:04.185 --> 00:56:09.356
and never feeling the rest of my whole life
the way I feel when I'm with you!

647
00:56:16.739 --> 00:56:19.575
<i>(Record player clicks)</i>

648
00:56:20.785 --> 00:56:23.788
<i>♪ ("Cry to me"
by Solomon Burke begins) ♪</i>

649
00:56:30.669 --> 00:56:32.588
Dance with me.

650
00:56:34.715 --> 00:56:37.718
- What, here?
- Here.

651
00:56:53.192 --> 00:56:56.195
<i>♪ ("Cry to Me"
continues playing) ♪</i>

652
00:59:21.548 --> 00:59:23.550
<i>(Birds chirping)</i>

653
00:59:38.315 --> 00:59:41.986
<i>(Stan) Singers, dancers, actors,
this is your lucky day!</i>

654
00:59:42.069 --> 00:59:45.030
<i>The auditions for the annual Kellerman
end-of-the-season talent show</i>

655
00:59:45.114 --> 00:59:47.866
<i>beginning in the playhouse.</i>

656
00:59:54.415 --> 00:59:57.292
- So everyone gonna be in the show?
- No, we're leaving tomorrow.

657
00:59:57.376 --> 00:59:59.503
Miss the weekend traffic.

658
00:59:59.586 --> 01:00:01.463
But Jake, we're paid up 'til Sunday.

659
01:00:01.547 --> 01:00:04.508
- Daddy! And miss the show?
- I said we're leaving tomorrow.

660
01:00:04.591 --> 01:00:05.968
But Daddy, I was going
to sing in the show.

661
01:00:06.051 --> 01:00:07.594
<i>(Neil)</i> It's the big event.

662
01:00:07.678 --> 01:00:08.929
People bring their own arrangements.

663
01:00:09.013 --> 01:00:11.765
You don't want to miss it.
Oh, Baby, I need you for props.

664
01:00:13.642 --> 01:00:15.310
Jake, why would you want
to leave early?

665
01:00:23.277 --> 01:00:26.613
It was just an idea.
We can stay if you want to.

666
01:00:29.825 --> 01:00:32.244
So, Lisa, what were you
planning to sing?

667
01:00:32.327 --> 01:00:33.871
"I Feel Pretty."

668
01:00:33.954 --> 01:00:36.415
Or "What Do the Simple Folk Do?"

669
01:00:36.498 --> 01:00:40.794
Or "I Feel Pretty."
What do you think, Daddy?

670
01:00:40.878 --> 01:00:42.880
<i>(Radio playing indistinct)</i>

671
01:00:48.844 --> 01:00:50.554
- <i>(Penny)</i> Hi.
- Hi.

672
01:00:52.347 --> 01:00:54.224
You look much better.

673
01:00:56.477 --> 01:01:00.522
You just missed your father.
He's such a wonderful man.

674
01:01:01.899 --> 01:01:04.902
I'm sorry. I didn't realize--

675
01:01:04.985 --> 01:01:07.321
No, you couldn't have. It's okay.

676
01:01:08.405 --> 01:01:09.448
<i>(Knock on door)</i>

677
01:01:10.866 --> 01:01:13.160
- Hey!
- Johnny.

678
01:01:19.333 --> 01:01:21.668
- So, how you doin'?
- I'm okay.

679
01:01:21.752 --> 01:01:23.170
Yeah?

680
01:01:23.253 --> 01:01:25.881
Dr. Houseman says
I'm going to be fine.

681
01:01:27.049 --> 01:01:28.550
I can still have children.

682
01:01:28.634 --> 01:01:31.303
Oh, Penny, that's great,
that's really great.

683
01:01:34.056 --> 01:01:36.642
So? How did it go last night?

684
01:01:36.725 --> 01:01:38.685
Good.

685
01:01:39.686 --> 01:01:44.483
Fine. I didn't do the lifts,
but it was good.

686
01:01:55.202 --> 01:01:59.331
Well, I guess I--
I guess I'm gonna go.

687
01:01:59.414 --> 01:02:00.749
Bye.

688
01:02:02.876 --> 01:02:03.710
See ya.

689
01:02:11.301 --> 01:02:13.011
So, he says you're
going to be fine?

690
01:02:13.095 --> 01:02:14.888
- Johnny, what are you doing?
- Don't worry about Max.

691
01:02:14.972 --> 01:02:16.223
I'll tell him your grandmother
died or something.

692
01:02:16.306 --> 01:02:18.642
How many times have you told me
never get mixed-up with them?

693
01:02:21.186 --> 01:02:22.479
I know what I'm doing, Penny.

694
01:02:23.480 --> 01:02:27.317
You listen to me.
You've got to stop it now.

695
01:02:42.791 --> 01:02:44.918
Look, um, I gotta run.

696
01:02:45.002 --> 01:02:46.503
I got a lesson with the Kramers
in three minutes,

697
01:02:46.587 --> 01:02:48.463
and they'll kill each other
if I'm not there.

698
01:02:48.547 --> 01:02:51.008
Well, sure. You've gotta go.

699
01:02:53.802 --> 01:02:55.095
I'll see ya.

700
01:02:58.265 --> 01:02:59.183
Johnny!

701
01:03:12.696 --> 01:03:14.656
<i>(Thunder rolling)</i>

702
01:03:14.740 --> 01:03:17.659
<i>(Stan) It's rainy day game time.
Pin the tail on the guest.</i>

703
01:03:17.743 --> 01:03:20.621
<i>Win ten boxes of Kleenex
or a billy goat!</i>

704
01:03:20.704 --> 01:03:24.708
God, I am so sick of this rain.

705
01:03:24.791 --> 01:03:27.461
Remind me not to take my honeymoon
at Niagara Falls.

706
01:03:27.544 --> 01:03:30.672
So, you go to Acapulco.
It'll be fine.

707
01:03:30.756 --> 01:03:34.426
Where is my beige iridescent lipstick?

708
01:03:34.509 --> 01:03:36.678
I know I put it in this drawer.

709
01:03:36.762 --> 01:03:38.972
Baby, where are you going
in this weather?

710
01:03:39.056 --> 01:03:42.100
Uh, they're having charades
in the west lobby.

711
01:03:42.184 --> 01:03:44.686
Quite the little joiner,
aren't we?

712
01:03:51.610 --> 01:03:54.613
<i>♪ ("Will You Love Me Tomorrow?"
by The Shirelles playing) ♪</i>

713
01:03:59.409 --> 01:04:02.913
- Have you had many women?
- What?

714
01:04:02.996 --> 01:04:05.499
Have you had many women?

715
01:04:05.582 --> 01:04:07.334
Baby, come on.

716
01:04:07.417 --> 01:04:10.295
- Tell me. I want to know.
- No! No!

717
01:04:10.379 --> 01:04:11.672
<i>(Scoffs)</i>

718
01:04:16.426 --> 01:04:18.553
<i>(Thunder rolls)</i>

719
01:04:20.430 --> 01:04:23.350
Look, you gotta understand
what it's like, Baby.

720
01:04:23.433 --> 01:04:25.352
You come from the streets
and suddenly you're up here,

721
01:04:25.435 --> 01:04:27.646
and these women, they are throwing
themselves at you,

722
01:04:27.729 --> 01:04:29.815
and they smell so good.

723
01:04:29.898 --> 01:04:31.358
And they really take care
of themselves.

724
01:04:31.441 --> 01:04:34.945
I mean, I never knew women
could be like that, you know?

725
01:04:35.028 --> 01:04:36.655
And they're so rich,
so goddamn rich

726
01:04:36.738 --> 01:04:38.282
that you think they must know
about everything.

727
01:04:38.365 --> 01:04:41.118
And they're slippin' their room keys
in my hand two or three times a day--

728
01:04:41.201 --> 01:04:44.538
Different women-- and so here I think
I'm scorin' big, right?

729
01:04:44.621 --> 01:04:46.832
For a while, you think, "Hey!

730
01:04:46.915 --> 01:04:49.835
They wouldn't be doing this
if they didn't care about me, right?"

731
01:04:49.918 --> 01:04:54.006
That's all right. I understand.
You were just using them, that's all.

732
01:04:55.882 --> 01:04:57.843
No! No, that's not it.

733
01:04:57.926 --> 01:05:00.637
That's the thing, Baby.
See, it wasn't like that.

734
01:05:02.681 --> 01:05:04.850
They were using me.

735
01:05:04.933 --> 01:05:06.935
<i>♪ ("Will You Still Love Me Tomorrow"
continues playing) ♪</i>

736
01:05:32.002 --> 01:05:33.837
What's your real name, Baby?

737
01:05:35.922 --> 01:05:40.552
Frances, for the first woman
in the Cabinet.

738
01:05:40.635 --> 01:05:42.220
<i>(Laughs)</i>

739
01:05:42.304 --> 01:05:46.600
Frances. That's a real grownup name.

740
01:05:53.565 --> 01:05:55.567
<i>(Crickets chirping)</i>

741
01:05:58.862 --> 01:06:01.448
I've decided to go
all the way with Robbie.

742
01:06:03.867 --> 01:06:07.537
Oh, Lisa, no!
Not with someone like him.

743
01:06:07.621 --> 01:06:12.000
Do you think if we came back here for
a 10th anniversary, it would be free?

744
01:06:12.084 --> 01:06:15.587
It's just wrong this way.
It should be with someone--

745
01:06:15.670 --> 01:06:20.217
It should be with someone that--
that you sort of love.

746
01:06:20.300 --> 01:06:23.887
Oh, come on.
You don't care about me.

747
01:06:24.888 --> 01:06:27.641
You wouldn't care if I humped
the entire army

748
01:06:27.724 --> 01:06:30.894
as long as they were on the right side
of the Ho Chi Minh Trail.

749
01:06:30.977 --> 01:06:34.564
What you care about is that
you're not Daddy's girl anymore.

750
01:06:35.857 --> 01:06:37.984
He listens when I talk now.

751
01:06:39.444 --> 01:06:41.154
You hate that.

752
01:06:53.458 --> 01:06:54.876
<i>(Whistle blowing)</i>

753
01:06:58.505 --> 01:07:00.632
<i>(Baby)</i> Two, three, cha-cha-cha.

754
01:07:00.715 --> 01:07:03.760
Hey, my frame!
Where's my pleasing arc?

755
01:07:03.844 --> 01:07:07.889
Spaghetti arms! Would you
give me some tension, please?

756
01:07:09.224 --> 01:07:12.602
You're invading my dance space.
This is my dance space.

757
01:07:12.686 --> 01:07:15.439
That's yours. Let's cha-cha.

758
01:07:21.236 --> 01:07:24.614
Don't look down.
Look right here.

759
01:07:30.454 --> 01:07:33.206
<i>(Lip-syncing) - Sylvia?
- Yes, Mickey?</i>

760
01:07:33.290 --> 01:07:36.001
<i>How you call your lover boy?</i>

761
01:07:36.084 --> 01:07:37.627
<i>Come here, lover boy.</i>

762
01:07:37.711 --> 01:07:41.673
<i>- And if he doesn’t answer?
- Oh, lover boy.</i>

763
01:07:41.756 --> 01:07:43.258
<i>And if he still doesn’t answer?</i>

764
01:07:43.341 --> 01:07:44.676
<i>I simply say...</i>

765
01:07:44.759 --> 01:07:47.512
<i>♪ Baby ♪</i>

766
01:07:47.596 --> 01:07:51.433
<i>♪ O-Oh, baby ♪</i>

767
01:07:51.516 --> 01:07:55.312
<i>♪ My sweet baby ♪</i>

768
01:07:55.395 --> 01:07:57.522
<i>♪ You're the one ♪</i>

769
01:08:05.489 --> 01:08:07.282
- Johnny!
- Yeah?

770
01:08:10.577 --> 01:08:11.953
<i>(Song volume lowers)</i>

771
01:08:12.037 --> 01:08:15.207
Baby, uh, you takin' dance lessons?

772
01:08:15.290 --> 01:08:17.209
I could teach ya, kid.

773
01:08:18.376 --> 01:08:19.503
<i>(Needle scratches record)</i>

774
01:08:21.463 --> 01:08:25.300
Uh... Johnny, my grandfather
put me in charge of the final show.

775
01:08:25.383 --> 01:08:27.302
I want to talk to you
about the last dance.

776
01:08:27.385 --> 01:08:30.472
I'd like to, uh,
shake things up a bit.

777
01:08:30.555 --> 01:08:32.307
- You know, move with the times.
- Yeah?

778
01:08:32.390 --> 01:08:35.268
- Yeah.
- I've got a lot of ideas.

779
01:08:35.352 --> 01:08:37.812
I've been working
with the staff kids

780
01:08:37.896 --> 01:08:40.607
on this, like, cross between
this Cuban rhythm and soul dancing.

781
01:08:40.690 --> 01:08:43.902
- It goes...
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, boy.

782
01:08:43.985 --> 01:08:45.570
Way over your head here.

783
01:08:45.654 --> 01:08:49.282
Now, I thought you always do
the mambo, huh?

784
01:08:50.367 --> 01:08:53.703
Why not dance
this year's final dance...

785
01:08:55.622 --> 01:08:57.374
to the pachanga?

786
01:08:58.667 --> 01:09:00.001
Right.

787
01:09:02.003 --> 01:09:05.882
Well, you're free to do the same
tired number as last year if you want,

788
01:09:05.966 --> 01:09:08.718
but next year we'll find
another dance person

789
01:09:08.802 --> 01:09:11.555
- who'll only be too happy--
- Sure, Neil. No problem.

790
01:09:13.390 --> 01:09:15.934
We'll end the season
with the pachanga.

791
01:09:16.017 --> 01:09:17.852
Great idea.

792
01:09:23.650 --> 01:09:27.988
Sometimes he's hard to talk to,
but the ladies seem to like him.

793
01:09:28.071 --> 01:09:31.116
See that he gives you the full half-hour
you're paying him for, kid.

794
01:09:33.743 --> 01:09:35.579
<i>(Footsteps depart)</i>

795
01:09:39.624 --> 01:09:43.003
That little wimp! He wouldn't know a new
idea if it hit him in the pachanga.

796
01:09:43.086 --> 01:09:45.380
He wants some new ideas?
I could have told him some new ideas.

797
01:09:45.463 --> 01:09:47.465
Well, why did you let him
talk to you that way?

798
01:09:47.549 --> 01:09:48.592
What do you mean,
fight the boss man?

799
01:09:48.675 --> 01:09:51.469
You tell him your ideas. He's a person,
like everyone else.

800
01:09:51.553 --> 01:09:52.846
Look, I know these people, Baby.

801
01:09:52.929 --> 01:09:55.640
They are rich and they're mean.
They won't listen to me.

802
01:09:55.724 --> 01:09:58.143
Well, then why not fight harder?
Make them listen.

803
01:09:58.226 --> 01:10:00.854
Because I need this goddamned job
lined up for next summer.

804
01:10:02.188 --> 01:10:05.150
My dad calls me today,
he says, "Good news"' you know?

805
01:10:05.233 --> 01:10:07.235
He says, "Uncle Paul can finally
get you in the union."

806
01:10:07.319 --> 01:10:08.778
What union?

807
01:10:09.863 --> 01:10:13.783
The House Painters and Plasterers,
Local Number 179, at your service.

808
01:10:17.203 --> 01:10:18.371
- <i>(Door opens)</i>
- <i>(Gasps)</i>

809
01:10:21.791 --> 01:10:24.044
I've been thinking a lot
about the domino theory.

810
01:10:24.127 --> 01:10:26.880
Now, when Vietnam falls,
is China Next?

811
01:10:30.133 --> 01:10:31.635
I don't think they saw us.

812
01:10:42.437 --> 01:10:44.856
Fight harder, huh?

813
01:10:44.939 --> 01:10:46.733
I don't see you fightin'
so hard, Baby.

814
01:10:46.816 --> 01:10:49.069
I don't see you running up to Daddy
and tellin' him I'm your guy.

815
01:10:49.152 --> 01:10:51.321
I will. With my father,
it's complicated.

816
01:10:51.404 --> 01:10:53.948
- I will tell him.
- I don't believe you, Baby.

817
01:10:57.118 --> 01:10:58.745
I don't think...

818
01:11:00.121 --> 01:11:02.749
that you ever had
any intention of telling him.

819
01:11:03.958 --> 01:11:05.210
Ever.

820
01:11:16.513 --> 01:11:19.307
<i>(Cousin Brucie) Well, cousins, it's almost over.
Labor Day weekend is here,</i>

821
01:11:19.391 --> 01:11:21.309
<i>and soon it's back to the old books
and back to work.</i>

822
01:11:21.393 --> 01:11:23.103
<i>Oh, what a terrible thought!</i>

823
01:11:23.186 --> 01:11:25.188
<i>(Indistinct chatter)</i>

824
01:11:32.487 --> 01:11:34.572
Hi, have you seen Johnny?

825
01:11:34.656 --> 01:11:36.658
<i>(Music playing on radio,
indistinct)</i>

826
01:11:50.213 --> 01:11:52.298
I'm sorry.

827
01:11:56.010 --> 01:11:58.263
Hey, well, it looks like I picked
the wrong sister.

828
01:11:58.346 --> 01:12:01.266
That's okay, Baby.
I went slummin' too.

829
01:12:01.349 --> 01:12:03.059
Oh, Johnny!

830
01:12:04.728 --> 01:12:05.937
- <i>(Groans)</i>
- <i>(Girls exclaim)</i>

831
01:12:10.900 --> 01:12:12.569
<i>(Grunting and groaning)</i>

832
01:12:18.450 --> 01:12:20.034
Hit me. Hit me.

833
01:12:21.244 --> 01:12:22.746
- <i>(Grunting)</i>
- <i>(Guys cheer)</i>

834
01:12:28.209 --> 01:12:29.711
Get out of here.
You're not worth it.

835
01:12:30.754 --> 01:12:32.213
You're not worth it.

836
01:12:33.256 --> 01:12:35.258
- <i>(Robbie coughs)</i>
- <i>(Johnny breathing hard)</i>

837
01:12:58.490 --> 01:13:02.994
<i>♪ Who's this Hula Hanna
of Kamana Wanna Hula Bay ♪</i>

838
01:13:05.330 --> 01:13:08.541
<i>♪ She will hula when you
have a lovely gift she wants ♪</i>

839
01:13:08.625 --> 01:13:10.543
<i>♪ You'll hear her say ♪</i>

840
01:13:12.837 --> 01:13:15.089
<i>♪ Bring me a pineapple
that doesn’t sting ♪</i>

841
01:13:15.173 --> 01:13:17.008
<i>♪ A bird that swims,
a fish that sings ♪</i>

842
01:13:17.091 --> 01:13:20.136
<i>♪ I want 'em, I really want 'me ♪</i>

843
01:13:20.220 --> 01:13:23.848
<i>♪ Bring me a volcano that
blows up all the molten jam-a ♪</i>

844
01:13:23.932 --> 01:13:27.477
-<i>♪ And a blue banana.</i> ♪</i>
- Hi, Vivian.

845
01:13:27.560 --> 01:13:30.605
Win big, Moe. As always.

846
01:13:30.688 --> 01:13:35.109
<i>♪... A fish that sings,
I want 'em, I really want 'me ♪</i>

847
01:13:35.193 --> 01:13:38.404
<i>♪ Bring me a volcano that
blows up all the molten jam-a ♪</i>

848
01:13:38.488 --> 01:13:42.450
<i>♪ And a blue banana, I can, I canna ♪</i>

849
01:13:42.534 --> 01:13:44.494
<i>♪ And you can wacka all you wanna ♪</i>

850
01:13:44.577 --> 01:13:48.581
<i>♪ While I hula all the day away ♪</i>

851
01:13:48.665 --> 01:13:50.250
This is our last night together, lover.

852
01:13:50.333 --> 01:13:52.627
I've got something worked out for us.

853
01:13:52.710 --> 01:13:55.421
<i>(Lisa) ♪ All the day away ♪</i>

854
01:13:57.257 --> 01:14:00.885
<i>♪ All the boys
of Okakokanoka Island ♪</i>

855
01:14:00.969 --> 01:14:04.639
<i>♪ Gathered all the gifts
that Hula Hanna asked ♪</i>

856
01:14:04.722 --> 01:14:08.351
<i>♪ They have combed their island
home fulfilling each whim ♪</i>

857
01:14:08.434 --> 01:14:11.896
<i>♪ And it's worth it when they
watch her shake her grass ♪</i>

858
01:14:11.980 --> 01:14:15.066
Four, five.<i>♪ Bring me
a gentle breeze. ♪</i></i>

859
01:14:15.149 --> 01:14:17.735
Excuse me, sir.
The pirate number's next.

860
01:14:17.819 --> 01:14:18.903
Oh, yeah, thanks.

861
01:14:18.987 --> 01:14:21.364
Hey, kid. Listen, you know,
I play cards all weekend

862
01:14:21.447 --> 01:14:22.782
and I've got an all-night game tonight.

863
01:14:22.866 --> 01:14:26.369
Why don't you give my wife
some extra dance lessons?

864
01:14:28.329 --> 01:14:29.414
<i>(Lisa) ♪ ...doesn’t sting ♪</i>

865
01:14:29.497 --> 01:14:31.124
<i>♪ A bird that swims,
a fish that sings ♪</i>

866
01:14:31.207 --> 01:14:34.210
<i>♪ I want 'em, I really want 'em ♪</i>

867
01:14:34.294 --> 01:14:36.129
Um...

868
01:14:36.212 --> 01:14:37.505
I'm sorry, Mr. Pressman,

869
01:14:37.589 --> 01:14:39.966
but I'm booked up the whole weekend here,
with the show and everything.

870
01:14:40.049 --> 01:14:42.010
So I won't have time
for anything else.

871
01:14:42.093 --> 01:14:44.053
I don't think it'd be fair
to take the money.

872
01:14:45.430 --> 01:14:49.726
<i>(Lisa) ♪ ...you can wacka
while I walk away ♪</i>

873
01:14:51.269 --> 01:14:53.187
<i>♪ And you can wacka all you wanna ♪</i>

874
01:14:53.271 --> 01:14:56.691
<i>♪ You can wacka while I walk away ♪</i>

875
01:14:56.774 --> 01:14:58.610
<i>♪ Away ♪</i>

876
01:14:58.693 --> 01:15:00.403
<i>(Higher pitch) ♪ Away ♪</i>

877
01:15:00.486 --> 01:15:03.114
<i>(Highest pitch) ♪ Away ♪</i>

878
01:15:03.197 --> 01:15:04.908
<i>(Song ends)</i>

879
01:15:10.079 --> 01:15:12.832
I've decided tonight's
the night with Robbie.

880
01:15:12.916 --> 01:15:14.626
He doesn't even know yet.

881
01:15:17.086 --> 01:15:18.546
Oh, hey, Lisa!

882
01:15:19.923 --> 01:15:22.926
<i>♪ ("Yes" by Merry Clayton
playing throughout) ♪</i>

883
01:15:49.535 --> 01:15:51.955
Robbie. It's me.

884
01:15:57.585 --> 01:15:58.836
<i>(Robbie)</i> Holy shit!

885
01:16:04.050 --> 01:16:04.884
<i>("Yes" stops)</i>

886
01:16:09.305 --> 01:16:12.308
<i>♪ ("In The Still of the Night"
by The Five Satins playing) ♪</i>

887
01:16:19.649 --> 01:16:21.484
You wanna hear somethin' crazy?

888
01:16:26.114 --> 01:16:27.573
Last night I...

889
01:16:28.741 --> 01:16:32.996
I dreamt we were walking along
and... we met your father,

890
01:16:33.079 --> 01:16:35.999
and he said, "Come on"
and he put his arm around me.

891
01:16:37.458 --> 01:16:39.252
Just like he did with Robbie.

892
01:16:43.673 --> 01:16:45.675
<i>♪ ("In The Still of the Night"
continues playing) ♪</i>

893
01:17:22.754 --> 01:17:24.756
<i>(Indistinct chatter)</i>

894
01:17:27.133 --> 01:17:32.388
You know how you feel when you see
a patient and you think he's all right,

895
01:17:32.472 --> 01:17:35.349
then you look at the X-rays
and it's nothing like you thought?

896
01:17:35.433 --> 01:17:36.434
What happened, Max?

897
01:17:36.517 --> 01:17:40.229
It's exactly what it's like when you
find out one of your staff's a thief.

898
01:17:40.313 --> 01:17:43.983
Moe Pressman's wallet was stolen when
he was playing pinochle last night.

899
01:17:44.067 --> 01:17:46.778
It was in his jacket hanging
on the back of his chair.

900
01:17:46.861 --> 01:17:48.362
He had it at 1:30,

901
01:17:48.446 --> 01:17:51.074
and when he checked again
at quarter of 4:00...

902
01:17:51.157 --> 01:17:52.408
it was missing.

903
01:17:53.951 --> 01:17:59.540
Vivian thinks she remembers
this dance kid, Johnny, walking by.

904
01:18:00.541 --> 01:18:04.420
So we ask him, "You have
an alibi for last night?"

905
01:18:04.504 --> 01:18:07.048
He says he was alone
in his room reading.

906
01:18:07.131 --> 01:18:08.341
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

907
01:18:08.424 --> 01:18:11.677
There are no books
in Johnny's room!

908
01:18:11.761 --> 01:18:14.597
There's been a mistake.
I know Johnny didn't do it.

909
01:18:14.680 --> 01:18:16.224
There's been similar thefts
at the Sheldrake.

910
01:18:16.307 --> 01:18:18.309
It's happened here before.
Three other wallets.

911
01:18:18.392 --> 01:18:20.895
- Well, I know he didn't do it.
- Stay out of it, Baby.

912
01:18:20.978 --> 01:18:22.980
- <i>(Table dragging across floor)</i>
- <i>(Max) Wait.</i>

913
01:18:23.064 --> 01:18:25.733
Don't put those tables together.
Come on.

914
01:18:27.902 --> 01:18:29.237
Daddy, I need your help.

915
01:18:29.320 --> 01:18:32.198
I know Johnny didn't take
Moe's wallet. I know.

916
01:18:32.281 --> 01:18:34.700
- Oh? How do you know?
- I can't tell you.

917
01:18:34.784 --> 01:18:39.580
- Just please trust me, Daddy.
- I'm sorry, Baby. I can't.

918
01:18:39.664 --> 01:18:41.499
This Danish is pure protein.

919
01:18:41.582 --> 01:18:43.000
Mr. Kellerman, look.

920
01:18:43.084 --> 01:18:44.502
Uh...

921
01:18:44.585 --> 01:18:47.964
Maybe Johnny didn't do it.
Anyone could've taken it.

922
01:18:48.047 --> 01:18:49.966
Maybe it was, uh--

923
01:18:50.049 --> 01:18:52.885
You know, it could've been that
little old couple, the Schumachers.

924
01:18:52.969 --> 01:18:56.514
- I saw her with a couple of wallets.
- Sylvia and Sidney?

925
01:18:56.597 --> 01:18:59.642
Baby, you don't go around
accusing innocent people.

926
01:18:59.725 --> 01:19:01.727
Yeah, but I saw them!
I even saw them at the Sheldrake.

927
01:19:01.811 --> 01:19:03.896
Didn't you say something
was stolen at the Sheldrake?

928
01:19:03.980 --> 01:19:07.567
I got an eyewitness
and the kid has no alibi.

929
01:19:07.650 --> 01:19:09.110
Come on, Neil.

930
01:19:09.193 --> 01:19:11.821
You'll learn what it's like
to fire an employee.

931
01:19:11.904 --> 01:19:13.489
No, Mr. Kellerman, wait a minute.

932
01:19:13.573 --> 01:19:16.242
I know Johnny didn't take the wallet.

933
01:19:16.325 --> 01:19:19.871
I know he didn't take it because
he was in his room all night.

934
01:19:19.954 --> 01:19:22.248
And the reason I know...

935
01:19:22.331 --> 01:19:24.500
is because I was with him.

936
01:19:29.005 --> 01:19:31.007
<i>(Birds chirping)</i>

937
01:19:48.566 --> 01:19:50.735
I told you I was telling
